Since the Java indices start at 0, in Fortran, if the array is 1-based, then the elements are nums(1) to nums(n). So when i is from 1 to n-1 (Java's i goes up to n-1, which is 1-based's up to n-1), so the equivalent in Fortran would loop from 2 to n? Wait, no: let's think: In Java:

for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) 

i runs from 1 to n-1 (since i < n). So the indices in nums are [i-1] and [i], so 0 to 1, etc., up to n-2 and n-1.
